          <div class="Header1">
            <span id="BM__Toc185328702_anchor" class="hyperlink-no-style"></span>
            <span style="font-size:16px; min-height:16px" dir="ltr">Appendix
 C: Background information for financial market participants that are 
users of the information produced using this Standard (reconciliation 
with other EU regulations)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="BasicnumberredN_MarginsClippedToRowHeight_MarginsClippedToRowHeight" style="text-indent:0; display:flex; margin-left:0px">
            <span class="numbering-583-level-0" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal" dir="ltr" id="id-548">
              <a href="#id-548">245.</a>
            </span>
            <span style="display:contents" dir="ltr">This appendix is 
relevant for users of the sustainability report. The table below 
illustrates the Sustainable Finance Datapoints that are present in 
different modules of this Standard that satisfy the requests of multiple
 user types (banks, investors, large undertakings).</span>
          </div>
          <div class="BasicnumberredN_MarginsClippedToRowHeight_MarginsClippedToRowHeight" style="text-indent:0; display:flex; margin-left:0px">
            <span class="numbering-583-level-0" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal" dir="ltr" id="id-549">
              <a href="#id-549">246.</a>
            </span>
            <span style="display:contents" dir="ltr">The column ‘DR 
number and Title’ identifies the disclosures present in the different 
modules (i.e. Basic Module, and Comprehensive Module) that are 
Sustainable Finance datapoints. The column SFDR Table 1 and/or EBA 
Pillar 3 and/or Benchmark Regulation illustrates how these disclosures 
relate to these regulations that are relevant for users of the 
sustainability report (banks, other investors).</span>
          </div>
          <table class="TableGrid" style="width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; margin:0px auto 0px 0px; " dir="ltr">
            <tr class="d6e7576">
              <td class="d3a5370">
